description.p:
Each patient should meet the following inclusion criteria to be treated in accordance with these regimens:


1. Documented ASM deficiency consistent with Niemann-Pick (N-P) disease;

2. Diffusing capacity (DLCO) >20% and ≤80% of the predicted normal value;

3. Spleen volume ≥8 times normal (≥1.6% of body weight);

4. Female patients of childbearing potential must have a serum pregnancy test negative for β-hCG, and agree to use a medically acceptable method of birth control for the duration of the protocol.
